.:: Puzzle 2x7-Level-8-2::.
7 different games are played: poker, monopoly, snooker, domino, backgammon, whist, bridge
City: liverpool, miami, san-francisco, nizza, hamburg, london, berlin
 1. the person traveling to hamburg is in the middle##1
 2. the person traveling to london is not the person playing snooker##6
 3. the person traveling to san-francisco is not to the left of the person traveling to liverpool##8
 4. the person traveling to london is between the person traveling to liverpool and the person playing snooker##2
 5. the person playing backgammon is in an odd position##4
 6. the person playing poker is on the right of the person traveling to nizza##1
 7. the person playing bridge is in an odd position##4
 8. the person traveling to san-francisco is not to the left of the person traveling to nizza##8
 9. the person playing whist is somewhere to the right of the person playing domino##5
10. the person traveling to nizza is on the left of the person traveling to san-francisco##1
11. the person playing poker is on the right of the person playing backgammon##1
12. the person traveling to miami is not to the right of the person traveling to nizza##8
13. the person playing domino is not to the left of the person playing bridge##8
14. the person traveling to nizza is somewhere to the right of the person traveling to hamburg##5
15. the person playing monopoly is on the left or right of the person traveling to nizza##3
16. the person playing snooker is on the left of the person traveling to hamburg##1

.:: Answer ::.
|         |    1    |    2    |     3      |    4    |     5      |      6      |      7      |
